<section class="calloutBox">
  <h2>What Most Gardeners Should Actually Use</h2>

  <p>
    Use fine insect mesh if you are dealing with carrot rust fly or want protection from multiple small pests. Use standard insect netting for cabbage moth if airflow and ease of use are a priority.
  </p>

  <p>
    Make sure the netting is installed securely and sealed at the edges, since gaps will reduce effectiveness regardless of mesh size.
  </p>

  <p class="muted">
    Match the mesh size to the pest, not just the crop.
  </p>
